msgid "tatiyepi satthavāse … "
msgstr "third, "

msgctxt "dn23:23.58"
msgid "catutthepi satthavāse … "
msgstr "fourth, "

msgctxt "dn23:23.59"
msgid "pañcamepi satthavāse … "
msgstr "fifth, "

msgctxt "dn23:23.60"
msgid "chaṭṭhepi satthavāse … "
msgstr "sixth, "

msgctxt "dn23:23.61"
msgid "sattamepi satthavāse na addasaṃsu tiṇaṃ vā kaṭṭhaṃ vā udakaṃ vā. "
msgstr "and seventh campsites they saw no grass, wood, or water. "

msgctxt "dn23:23.62"
msgid "Tañca satthaṃ addasaṃsu anayabyasanaṃ āpannaṃ. "
msgstr "And they saw the other caravan that had come to ruin. "

msgctxt "dn23:23.63"
msgid "Ye ca tasmiṃ satthepi ahesuṃ manussā vā pasū vā, tesañca aṭṭhikāneva addasaṃsu tena yakkhena amanussena bhakkhitānaṃ. "
msgstr "And they saw the bones of the men and beasts who had been devoured by that non-human spirit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc36
msgctxt "dn23:23.64"
msgid "Atha kho so satthavāho satthike āmantesi: "
msgstr "So the caravan leader addressed his drivers, "

msgctxt "dn23:23.65"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho, bho, sattho anayabyasanaṃ āpanno, yathā taṃ tena bālena satthavāhena pariṇāyakena. "
msgstr "‘This caravan came to ruin, as happens when guided by a foolish caravan leader. "

msgctxt "dn23:23.66"
msgid "Tena hi, bho, yānamhākaṃ satthe appasārāni paṇiyāni, tāni chaḍḍetvā, yāni imasmiṃ satthe mahāsārāni paṇiyāni, tāni ādiyathā’ti. "
msgstr "Well then, sirs, toss out any of our merchandise that’s of little value, and take what’s valuable from this caravan.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:23.67"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, bho’ti kho te satthikā tassa satthavāhassa paṭissutvā yāni sakasmiṃ satthe appasārāni paṇiyāni, tāni chaḍḍetvā yāni tasmiṃ satthe mahāsārāni paṇiyāni, tāni ādiyitvā sotthinā taṃ kantāraṃ nitthariṃsu, yathā taṃ paṇḍitena satthavāhena pariṇāyakena. "
msgstr "‘Yes, sir’ replied the drivers, and that’s what they did. They crossed over the desert safely, as happens when guided by an astute caravan leader. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:23.68"
msgid "Evameva kho tvaṃ, rājañña, bālo abyatto anayabyasanaṃ āpajjissasi ayoniso paralokaṃ gavesanto, seyyathāpi so purimo satthavāho. "
msgstr "In the same way, chieftain, being foolish and incompetent, you will come to ruin seeking the other world irrationally, like the first caravan leader. "

#. VAR: saddhātabbaṃ → saddahātabbaṃ (bj, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: tava → te (mr)
msgctxt "dn23:23.69"
msgid "Yepi tava sotabbaṃ saddhātabbaṃ maññissanti, tepi anayabyasanaṃ āpajjissanti, seyyathāpi te satthikā. "
msgstr "And those who think you’re worth listening to and trusting will also come to ruin, like the drivers. "

msgctxt "dn23:23.70"
msgid "Paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ; paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ. "
msgstr "Let go of this harmful misconception, chieftain, let go of it! "

msgctxt "dn23:23.71"
msgid "Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Don’t create lasting harm and suffering for yourself!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs24, pts-vp-pli2.347, sc37
msgctxt "dn23:24.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho nevāhaṃ sakkomi idaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ paṭinissajjituṃ. "
msgstr "“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I’m not able to let go of that harmful misconception. "

msgctxt "dn23:24.2"
msgid "Rājāpi maṃ pasenadi kosalo jānāti tirorājānopi: ‘pāyāsi rājañño evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhī: "
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala knows my views, and so do foreign kings. "

msgctxt "dn23:24.3"
msgid "“itipi natthi paro loko … pe … vipāko”’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:24.4"
msgid "Sacāhaṃ, bho kassapa, idaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ paṭinissajjissāmi, bhavissanti me vattāro: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:24.5"
msgid "‘yāva bālo pāyāsi rājañño, abyatto duggahitagāhī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:24.6"
msgid "Kopenapi naṃ harissāmi, makkhenapi naṃ harissāmi, palāsenapi naṃ harissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "I shall carry on with this view out of anger, contempt, and spite!” "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:24.7"
msgid "2.12. Gūthabhārikaupamā "
msgstr "2.12. The Simile of the Dung-Carrier "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs25, pts-vp-pli2.348, sc38
msgctxt "dn23:25.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi. "
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile. "

msgctxt "dn23:25.2"
msgid "Upamāya m’idhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti. "
msgstr "For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:25.3"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, rājañña, aññataro sūkaraposako puriso sakamhā gāmā aññaṃ gāmaṃ agamāsi. "
msgstr "Once upon a time, a certain swineherd went from his own village to another village. "

msgctxt "dn23:25.4"
msgid "Tattha addasa pahūtaṃ sukkhagūthaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ. "
msgstr "There he saw a large pile of dry dung abandoned. "

msgctxt "dn23:25.5"
msgid "Disvānassa etadahosi: "
msgstr "He thought, "

#. VAR: sūkarabhattaṃ → sūkarānaṃ bhakkho (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:25.6"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho pahūto sukkhagūtho chaḍḍito, mama ca sūkarabhattaṃ; "
msgstr "‘This pile of dry dung can serve as food for my pigs. "

msgctxt "dn23:25.7"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ ito sukkhagūthaṃ hareyyan’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I carry it off?’ "

#. VAR: ubbāhetvā → uccoropetvā (s1-3, km) | uccāropetvā (mr)
msgctxt "dn23:25.8"
msgid "So uttarāsaṅgaṃ pattharitvā pahūtaṃ sukkhagūthaṃ ākiritvā bhaṇḍikaṃ bandhitvā sīse ubbāhetvā agamāsi. "
msgstr "So he spread out his upper robe, shoveled the dry dung onto it, tied it up into a bundle, lifted it on to his head, and went on his way. "

msgctxt "dn23:25.9"
msgid "Tassa antarāmagge mahāakālamegho pāvassi. "
msgstr "While on his way a large sudden storm poured down. "

msgctxt "dn23:25.10"
msgid "So uggharantaṃ paggharantaṃ yāva agganakhā gūthena makkhito gūthabhāraṃ ādāya agamāsi. "
msgstr "Smeared with leaking, oozing dung down to his fingernails, he kept on carrying the load of dung. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:25.11"
msgid "Tamenaṃ manussā disvā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "When people saw him they said, "

msgctxt "dn23:25.12"
msgid "‘kacci no tvaṃ, bhaṇe, ummatto, kacci viceto, kathañhi nāma uggharantaṃ paggharantaṃ yāva agganakhā gūthena makkhito gūthabhāraṃ harissasī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Have you gone mad, sir? Have you lost your mind? For how can you, smeared with leaking, oozing dung down to your fingernails, keep on carrying that load of dung?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:25.13"
msgid "‘Tumhe khvettha, bhaṇe, ummattā, tumhe vicetā, tathā hi pana me sūkarabhattan’ti. "
msgstr "‘You’re the mad ones, sirs! You’re the ones who’ve lost your minds! For this will serve as food for my pigs.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:25.14"
msgid "Evameva kho tvaṃ, rājañña, gūthabhārikūpamo maññe paṭibhāsi. "
msgstr "In the same way, chieftain, you seem like the dung carrier in the simile. "

msgctxt "dn23:25.15"
msgid "Paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ; paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ. "
msgstr "Let go of this harmful misconception, chieftain, let go of it! "

msgctxt "dn23:25.16"
msgid "Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Don’t create lasting harm and suffering for yourself!” "

