msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:26.6"
msgid "‘yāva bālo pāyāsi rājañño abyatto duggahitagāhī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:26.7"
msgid "Kopenapi naṃ harissāmi, makkhenapi naṃ harissāmi, palāsenapi naṃ harissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "I shall carry on with this view out of anger, contempt, and spite!” "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:26.8"
msgid "2.13. Akkhadhuttakaupamā "
msgstr "2.13. The Simile of the Gamblers "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs27, pts-vp-pli2.349, sc40
msgctxt "dn23:27.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi, "
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile. "

msgctxt "dn23:27.2"
msgid "upamāya m’idhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti. "
msgstr "For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:27.3"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, rājañña, dve akkhadhuttā akkhehi dibbiṃsu. "
msgstr "Once upon a time, two gamblers were playing with dice. "

msgctxt "dn23:27.4"
msgid "Eko akkhadhutto āgatāgataṃ kaliṃ gilati. "
msgstr "One gambler, every time they made a bad throw, swallowed the dice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:27.5"
msgid "Addasā kho dutiyo akkhadhutto taṃ akkhadhuttaṃ āgatāgataṃ kaliṃ gilantaṃ, disvā taṃ akkhadhuttaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "The second gambler saw him, and said, "

# NOTE: Comm says “Pajjohissāmīti pajjohanaṃ karissāmi, balikammaṃ karissāmīti attho”, which is followed by RD and MW. Tika says “Pajjohananti pakārehi juhanakammaṃ. Taṃ pana balidānavasena karīyatīti āha ‘‘balikamma’’nti.” DA 7, instead, simply has 今日且停，明當更共試.
msgctxt "dn23:27.6"
msgid "‘tvaṃ kho, samma, ekantikena jināsi, dehi me, samma, akkhe pajohissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Well, my friend, you’ve won it all! Give me the dice, I will offer them as sacrifice.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:27.7"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, sammā’ti kho so akkhadhutto tassa akkhadhuttassa akkhe pādāsi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, my friend,’ the gambler replied, and gave them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:27.8"
msgid "Atha kho so akkhadhutto akkhe visena paribhāvetvā taṃ akkhadhuttaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Having soaked the dice in poison, the gambler said to the other, "

msgctxt "dn23:27.9"
msgid "‘ehi kho, samma, akkhehi dibbissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Come, my friend, let’s play dice.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:27.10"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, sammā’ti kho so akkhadhutto tassa akkhadhuttassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, my friend,’ the other gambler replied. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:27.11"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho te akkhadhuttā akkhehi dibbiṃsu. "
msgstr "And for a second time the gamblers played with dice. "

msgctxt "dn23:27.12"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho so akkhadhutto āgatāgataṃ kaliṃ gilati. "
msgstr "And for the second time, every time they made a bad throw, that gambler swallowed the dice. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:27.13"
msgid "Addasā kho dutiyo akkhadhutto taṃ akkhadhuttaṃ dutiyampi āgatāgataṃ kaliṃ gilantaṃ, disvā taṃ akkhadhuttaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "The second gambler saw him, and said, "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "dn23:27.14"
msgid "‘Littaṃ paramena tejasā, "
msgstr "‘The man swallows the dice without realizing "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn23:27.15"
msgid "Gilamakkhaṃ puriso na bujjhati; "
msgstr "they’re smeared with burning poison. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: gila pāpadhuttaka → gilare pāpadhuttā (s1-3, km) | gili re pāpadhuttaka (mr)
msgctxt "dn23:27.16"
msgid "Gila re gila pāpadhuttaka, "
msgstr "Swallow, you bloody cheat, swallow! "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Pacchā → kapaṇā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:27.17"
msgid "Pacchā te kaṭukaṃ bhavissatī’ti. "
msgstr "Soon you’ll know the bitter fruit!’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc42
msgctxt "dn23:27.18"
msgid "Evameva kho tvaṃ, rājañña, akkhadhuttakūpamo maññe paṭibhāsi. "
msgstr "In the same way, chieftain, you seem like the gambler in the simile. "

msgctxt "dn23:27.19"
msgid "Paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ; paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ. "
msgstr "Let go of this harmful misconception, chieftain, let go of it! "

msgctxt "dn23:27.20"
msgid "Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Don’t create lasting harm and suffering for yourself!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs28, sc43
msgctxt "dn23:28.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ kassapo evamāha, atha kho nevāhaṃ sakkomi idaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ paṭinissajjituṃ. "
msgstr "“Even though Master Kassapa says this, still I’m not able to let go of that harmful misconception. "

msgctxt "dn23:28.2"
msgid "Rājāpi maṃ pasenadi kosalo jānāti tirorājānopi: "
msgstr "King Pasenadi of Kosala knows my views, and so do foreign kings. "

msgctxt "dn23:28.3"
msgid "‘pāyāsi rājañño evaṃvādī evaṃdiṭṭhī: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:28.4"
msgid "“itipi natthi paro loko … pe … vipāko”’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:28.5"
msgid "Sacāhaṃ, bho kassapa, idaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ paṭinissajjissāmi, bhavissanti me vattāro: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:28.6"
msgid "‘yāva bālo pāyāsi rājañño abyatto duggahitagāhī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:28.7"
msgid "Kopenapi naṃ harissāmi, makkhenapi naṃ harissāmi, palāsenapi naṃ harissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "I shall carry on with this view out of anger, contempt, and spite!” "

#. HTML: </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn23:28.8"
msgid "2.14. Sāṇabhārikaupamā "
msgstr "2.14. The Simile of the Man Who Carried Hemp "

#. HTML: </h3><p>
#. REF: pts-cs29, pts-vp-pli2.350, sc44
msgctxt "dn23:29.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājañña, upamaṃ te karissāmi, "
msgstr "“Well then, chieftain, I shall give you a simile. "

msgctxt "dn23:29.2"
msgid "upamāya m’idhekacce viññū purisā bhāsitassa atthaṃ ājānanti. "
msgstr "For by means of a simile some sensible people understand the meaning of what is said. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:29.3"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, rājañña, aññataro janapado vuṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "Once upon a time, the inhabitants of a certain country emigrated. "

msgctxt "dn23:29.4"
msgid "Atha kho sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then one friend said to another, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.5"
msgid "‘āyāma, samma, yena so janapado tenupasaṅkamissāma, appeva nāmettha kiñci dhanaṃ adhigaccheyyāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Come, my friend, let’s go to that country. Hopefully we’ll get some riches there!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:29.6"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, sammā’ti kho sahāyako sahāyakassa paccassosi. "
msgstr "‘Yes, my friend,’ the other replied. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: Comm: “Gāmapaṭṭanti vuṭṭhitagāmapadeso vuccati. ‘‘Gāmapada’’ntipi pāṭho, ayamevattho”
#. VAR: gāmapaṭṭaṃ → gāmapatthaṃ (bj) | gāmapajjaṃ (s1-3) | gāmapaddhanaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:29.7"
msgid "Te yena so janapado, yena aññataraṃ gāmapaṭṭaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu, tattha addasaṃsu pahūtaṃ sāṇaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "They went to that country, and to a certain place in a village. There they saw a pile of abandoned sunn hemp. Seeing it, one friend said to the other, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.8"
msgid "‘idaṃ kho, samma, pahūtaṃ sāṇaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, tena hi, samma, tvañca sāṇabhāraṃ bandha, ahañca sāṇabhāraṃ bandhissāmi, ubho sāṇabhāraṃ ādāya gamissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is a pile of abandoned sunn hemp. Well then, my friend, you make up a bundle of hemp, and I’ll make one too. Let’s both take a bundle of hemp and go on.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:29.9"
msgid "‘Evaṃ, sammā’ti kho sahāyako sahāyakassa paṭissutvā sāṇabhāraṃ bandhitvā te ubho sāṇabhāraṃ ādāya yena aññataraṃ gāmapaṭṭaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "‘Yes, my friend,’ he said. Carrying their bundles of hemp they went to another place in the village. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:29.10"
msgid "Tattha addasaṃsu pahūtaṃ sāṇasuttaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "There they saw much sunn hemp thread abandoned. Seeing it, one friend said to the other, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.11"
msgid "‘yassa kho, samma, atthāya iccheyyāma sāṇaṃ, idaṃ pahūtaṃ sāṇasuttaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ. "
msgstr "‘This pile of abandoned sunn hemp thread is just what we wanted the hemp for! "

msgctxt "dn23:29.12"
msgid "Tena hi, samma, tvañca sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍehi, ahañca sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍessāmi, ubho sāṇasuttabhāraṃ ādāya gamissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Well then, my friend, let’s abandon our bundles of hemp, and both take a bundle of hemp thread and go on.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
# NOTE: The sunk cost fallacy!
msgctxt "dn23:29.13"
msgid "‘Ayaṃ kho me, samma, sāṇabhāro dūrābhato ca susannaddho ca, alaṃ me, tvaṃ pajānāhī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I’ve already carried this bundle of hemp a long way, and it’s well tied up. It’s good enough for me, you understand.’ "

msgctxt "dn23:29.14"
msgid "Atha kho so sahāyako sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍetvā sāṇasuttabhāraṃ ādiyi. "
msgstr "So one friend abandoned their bundle of hemp and picked up a bundle of hemp thread. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc45
msgctxt "dn23:29.15"
msgid "Te yena aññataraṃ gāmapaṭṭaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "They went to another place in the village. "

msgctxt "dn23:29.16"
msgid "Tattha addasaṃsu pahūtā sāṇiyo chaḍḍitā, disvā sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "There they saw much sunn hemp cloth abandoned. Seeing it, one friend said to the other, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.17"
msgid "‘yassa kho, samma, atthāya iccheyyāma sāṇaṃ vā sāṇasuttaṃ vā, imā pahūtā sāṇiyo chaḍḍitā. "
msgstr "‘This pile of abandoned sunn hemp cloth is just what we wanted the hemp and hemp thread for! "

msgctxt "dn23:29.18"
msgid "Tena hi, samma, tvañca sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍehi, ahañca sāṇasuttabhāraṃ chaḍḍessāmi, ubho sāṇibhāraṃ ādāya gamissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Well then, my friend, let’s abandon our bundles, and both take a bundle of hemp cloth and go on.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:29.19"
msgid "‘Ayaṃ kho me, samma, sāṇabhāro dūrābhato ca susannaddho ca, alaṃ me, tvaṃ pajānāhī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I’ve already carried this bundle of hemp a long way, and it’s well tied up. It’s good enough for me, you understand.’ "

msgctxt "dn23:29.20"
msgid "Atha kho so sahāyako sāṇasuttabhāraṃ chaḍḍetvā sāṇibhāraṃ ādiyi. "
msgstr "So one friend abandoned their bundle of hemp thread and picked up a bundle of hemp cloth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.351, sc46
msgctxt "dn23:29.21"
msgid "Te yena aññataraṃ gāmapaṭṭaṃ tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "They went to another place in the village. "

msgctxt "dn23:29.22"
msgid "Tattha addasaṃsu pahūtaṃ khomaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … pe … "
msgstr "There they saw a pile of flax, and by turn, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.23"
msgid "pahūtaṃ khomasuttaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "linen thread, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.24"
msgid "pahūtaṃ khomadussaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "linen cloth, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.25"
msgid "pahūtaṃ kappāsaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "silk, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.26"
msgid "pahūtaṃ kappāsikasuttaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "silk thread, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.27"
msgid "pahūtaṃ kappāsikadussaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "silk cloth, "

#. VAR: ayaṃ → ayasaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:29.28"
msgid "pahūtaṃ ayaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "iron, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.29"
msgid "pahūtaṃ lohaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "copper, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.30"
msgid "pahūtaṃ tipuṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "tin, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.31"
msgid "pahūtaṃ sīsaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "lead, "

#. VAR: sajjhaṃ → sajjhuṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:29.32"
msgid "pahūtaṃ sajjhaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā … "
msgstr "silver, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.33"
msgid "pahūtaṃ suvaṇṇaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ, disvā sahāyako sahāyakaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "and gold abandoned. Seeing it, one friend said to the other, "

msgctxt "dn23:29.34"
msgid "‘yassa kho, samma, atthāya iccheyyāma sāṇaṃ vā sāṇasuttaṃ vā sāṇiyo vā khomaṃ vā khomasuttaṃ vā khomadussaṃ vā kappāsaṃ vā kappāsikasuttaṃ vā kappāsikadussaṃ vā ayaṃ vā lohaṃ vā tipuṃ vā sīsaṃ vā sajjhaṃ vā, idaṃ pahūtaṃ suvaṇṇaṃ chaḍḍitaṃ. "
msgstr "‘This pile of gold is just what we wanted all those other things for! "

#. VAR: sajjhabhāraṃ → sajjhuṃ (bj) | sajjhubhāraṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:29.35"
msgid "Tena hi, samma, tvañca sāṇabhāraṃ chaḍḍehi, ahañca sajjhabhāraṃ chaḍḍessāmi, ubho suvaṇṇabhāraṃ ādāya gamissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Well then, my friend, let’s abandon our bundles, and both take a bundle of gold and go on.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:29.36"
msgid "‘Ayaṃ kho me, samma, sāṇabhāro dūrābhato ca susannaddho ca, alaṃ me tvaṃ pajānāhī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I’ve already carried this bundle of hemp a long way, and it’s well tied up. It’s good enough for me, you understand.’ "

msgctxt "dn23:29.37"
msgid "Atha kho so sahāyako sajjhabhāraṃ chaḍḍetvā suvaṇṇabhāraṃ ādiyi. "
msgstr "So one friend abandoned their bundle of silver and picked up a bundle of gold. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.352, sc47
msgctxt "dn23:29.38"
msgid "Te yena sako gāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then they returned to their own village. "

msgctxt "dn23:29.39"
msgid "Tattha yo so sahāyako sāṇabhāraṃ ādāya agamāsi, tassa neva mātāpitaro abhinandiṃsu, na puttadārā abhinandiṃsu, na mittāmaccā abhinandiṃsu, na ca tatonidānaṃ sukhaṃ somanassaṃ adhigacchi. "
msgstr "When one friend returned with a bundle of sunn hemp, they didn’t please their parents, their partners and children, or their friends and colleagues. And they got no pleasure and happiness on that account. "

msgctxt "dn23:29.40"
msgid "Yo pana so sahāyako suvaṇṇabhāraṃ ādāya agamāsi, tassa mātāpitaropi abhinandiṃsu, puttadārāpi abhinandiṃsu, mittāmaccāpi abhinandiṃsu, tatonidānañca sukhaṃ somanassaṃ adhigacchi. "
msgstr "But when the other friend returned with a bundle of gold, they pleased their parents, their partners and children, and their friends and colleagues. And they got much pleasure and happiness on that account. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:29.41"
msgid "Evameva kho tvaṃ, rājañña, sāṇabhārikūpamo maññe paṭibhāsi. "
msgstr "In the same way, chieftain, you seem like the hemp-carrier in the simile. "

msgctxt "dn23:29.42"
msgid "Paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ; paṭinissajjetaṃ, rājañña, pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ. "
msgstr "Let go of this harmful misconception, chieftain, let go of it! "

msgctxt "dn23:29.43"
msgid "Mā te ahosi dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Don’t create lasting harm and suffering for yourself!” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:29.44"
msgid "3. Saraṇagamana "
msgstr "3. Going for Refuge "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs30, sc48
msgctxt "dn23:30.1"
msgid "“Purimeneva ahaṃ opammena bhoto kassapassa attamano abhiraddho. "
msgstr "“I was delighted and satisfied with your very first simile, Master Kassapa! "

msgctxt "dn23:30.2"
msgid "Api cāhaṃ imāni vicitrāni pañhāpaṭibhānāni sotukāmo evāhaṃ bhavantaṃ kassapaṃ paccanīkaṃ kātabbaṃ amaññissaṃ. "
msgstr "Nevertheless, I wanted to hear your various solutions to the problem, so I thought I’d oppose you in this way. "

msgctxt "dn23:30.3"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho kassapa, abhikkantaṃ, bho kassapa. "
msgstr "Excellent, Master Kassapa! Excellent! "

msgctxt "dn23:30.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho kassapa, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā kassapena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Kassapa has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "dn23:30.5"
msgid "Esāhaṃ, bho kassapa, taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca, bhikkhusaṅghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "dn23:30.6"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ kassapo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ. "
msgstr "From this day forth, may Master Kassapa remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc49
msgctxt "dn23:30.7"
msgid "Icchāmi cāhaṃ, bho kassapa, mahāyaññaṃ yajituṃ, anusāsatu maṃ bhavaṃ kassapo, yaṃ mamassa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Master Kassapa, I wish to perform a great sacrifice. Please instruct me so it will be for my lasting welfare and happiness. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:30.8"
msgid "4. Yaññakathā "
msgstr "4. On Sacrifice "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs31, pts-vp-pli2.353, sc50
msgctxt "dn23:31.1"
msgid "“Yathārūpe kho, rājañña, yaññe gāvo vā haññanti ajeḷakā vā haññanti, kukkuṭasūkarā vā haññanti, vividhā vā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti, paṭiggāhakā ca honti micchādiṭṭhī micchāsaṅkappā micchāvācā micchākammantā micchāājīvā micchāvāyāmā micchāsatī micchāsamādhī, evarūpo kho, rājañña, yañño na mahapphalo hoti na mahānisaṃso na mahājutiko na mahāvipphāro. "
msgstr "“Chieftain, take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and various kinds of creatures are slaughtered. And the recipients have wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion. That kind of sacrifice is not very fruitful or beneficial or splendid or bountiful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:31.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājañña, kassako bījanaṅgalaṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya. "
msgstr "Suppose a farmer was to enter a wood taking seed and plough. "

msgctxt "dn23:31.3"
msgid "So tattha dukkhette dubbhūme avihatakhāṇukaṇṭake bījāni patiṭṭhāpeyya khaṇḍāni pūtīni vātātapahatāni asāradāni asukhasayitāni. "
msgstr "And on that barren field, that barren ground, with uncleared stumps he sowed seeds that were broken, spoiled, weather-damaged, infertile, and ill kept. "

msgctxt "dn23:31.4"
msgid "Devo ca na kālena kālaṃ sammādhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya. "
msgstr "And the heavens don’t provide enough rain when needed. "

#. VAR: virūḷhiṃ → verūḷhiṃ (bj) | viruḷhiṃ (s1-3, km moggalāne)
msgctxt "dn23:31.5"
msgid "Api nu tāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ, kassako vā vipulaṃ phalaṃ adhigaccheyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Would those seeds grow, increase, and mature, and would the farmer get abundant fruit?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: hidaṃ → na evaṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:31.6"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho kassapa”. "
msgstr "“No, Master Kassapa.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "dn23:31.7"
msgid "“Evameva kho, rājañña, yathārūpe yaññe gāvo vā haññanti, ajeḷakā vā haññanti, kukkuṭasūkarā vā haññanti, vividhā vā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti, paṭiggāhakā ca honti micchādiṭṭhī micchāsaṅkappā micchāvācā micchākammantā micchāājīvā micchāvāyāmā micchāsatī micchāsamādhī, evarūpo kho, rājañña, yañño na mahapphalo hoti na mahānisaṃso na mahājutiko na mahāvipphāro. "
msgstr "“In the same way, chieftain, take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and various kinds of creatures are slaughtered. And the recipients have wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, and wrong immersion. That kind of sacrifice is not very fruitful or beneficial or splendid or bountiful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.354, sc52
msgctxt "dn23:31.8"
msgid "Yathārūpe ca kho, rājañña, yaññe neva gāvo haññanti, na ajeḷakā haññanti, na kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, na vividhā vā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti, paṭiggāhakā ca honti sammādiṭṭhī sammāsaṅkappā sammāvācā sammākammantā sammāājīvā sammāvāyāmā sammāsatī sammāsamādhī, evarūpo kho, rājañña, yañño mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso mahājutiko mahāvipphāro. "
msgstr "But take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and various kinds of creatures are not slaughtered. And the recipients have right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. That kind of sacrifice is very fruitful and beneficial and splendid and bountiful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:31.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājañña, kassako bījanaṅgalaṃ ādāya vanaṃ paviseyya. "
msgstr "Suppose a farmer was to enter a wood taking seed and plough. "

msgctxt "dn23:31.10"
msgid "So tattha sukhette subhūme suvihatakhāṇukaṇṭake bījāni patiṭṭhapeyya akhaṇḍāni apūtīni avātātapahatāni sāradāni sukhasayitāni. "
msgstr "And on that fertile field, that fertile ground, with well-cleared stumps he sowed seeds that were intact, unspoiled, not weather-damaged, fertile, and well kept. "

msgctxt "dn23:31.11"
msgid "Devo ca kālena kālaṃ sammādhāraṃ anuppaveccheyya. "
msgstr "And the heavens provide plenty of rain when needed. "

msgctxt "dn23:31.12"
msgid "Api nu tāni bījāni vuddhiṃ virūḷhiṃ vepullaṃ āpajjeyyuṃ, kassako vā vipulaṃ phalaṃ adhigaccheyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Would those seeds grow, increase, and mature, and would the farmer get abundant fruit?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:31.13"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho kassapa”. "
msgstr "“Yes, Master Kassapa.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:31.14"
msgid "“Evameva kho, rājañña, yathārūpe yaññe neva gāvo haññanti, na ajeḷakā haññanti, na kukkuṭasūkarā haññanti, na vividhā vā pāṇā saṅghātaṃ āpajjanti, paṭiggāhakā ca honti sammādiṭṭhī sammāsaṅkappā sammāvācā sammākammantā sammāājīvā sammāvāyāmā sammāsatī sammāsamādhī, evarūpo kho, rājañña, yañño mahapphalo hoti mahānisaṃso mahājutiko mahāvipphāro”ti. "
msgstr "“In the same way, chieftain, take the kind of sacrifice where cattle, goats and sheep, chickens and pigs, and various kinds of creatures are not slaughtered. And the recipients have right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. That kind of sacrifice is very fruitful and beneficial and splendid and bountiful.” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:31.15"
msgid "5. Uttaramāṇavavatthu "
msgstr "5. On the Brahmin Student Uttara "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs32, pts-vp-pli2.355, sc53
msgctxt "dn23:32.1"
msgid "Atha kho pāyāsi rājañño dānaṃ paṭṭhapesi samaṇabrāhmaṇakapaṇaddhikavaṇibbakayācakānaṃ. "
msgstr "Then the chieftain Pāyāsi set up an offering for ascetics and brahmins, for paupers, vagrants, travelers, and beggars. "

# NOTE: Read dhorakani, from dhura (comm thūlāni). For guḷavālakāni, cp. Kd 15 which has macchavāḷaka for a monk’s (forbidden) robe. It doesn’t make it particularly clear, but at least it’s something.
#. VAR: dhorakāni → corakāni (s1-3, km) | therakāni (pts1)
#. VAR: guḷavālakāni → guḷagāḷakāni (bj, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:32.2"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana dāne evarūpaṃ bhojanaṃ dīyati kaṇājakaṃ bilaṅgadutiyaṃ, dhorakāni ca vatthāni guḷavālakāni. "
msgstr "At that offering such food as rough gruel with pickles was given, and heavy clothes with ball-tails. "

#. VAR: vāvaṭo → byāvaṭo (bj) | vyāvaṭo (pts1)
msgctxt "dn23:32.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana dāne uttaro nāma māṇavo vāvaṭo ahosi. "
msgstr "Now, it was a brahmin student named Uttara who organized that offering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:32.4"
msgid "So dānaṃ datvā evaṃ anuddisati: "
msgstr "When the offering was over he referred to it like this, "

msgctxt "dn23:32.5"
msgid "“imināhaṃ dānena pāyāsiṃ rājaññameva imasmiṃ loke samāgacchiṃ, mā parasmin”ti. "
msgstr "“Through this offering may I be together with the chieftain Pāyāsi in this world, but not in the next.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:32.6"
msgid "Assosi kho pāyāsi rājañño: "
msgstr "Pāyāsi heard of this, "

msgctxt "dn23:32.7"
msgid "“uttaro kira māṇavo dānaṃ datvā evaṃ anuddisati: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:32.8"
msgid "‘imināhaṃ dānena pāyāsiṃ rājaññameva imasmiṃ loke samāgacchiṃ, mā parasmin’”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:32.9"
msgid "Atha kho pāyāsi rājañño uttaraṃ māṇavaṃ āmantāpetvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "so he summoned Uttara and said, "

msgctxt "dn23:32.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, tāta uttara, dānaṃ datvā evaṃ anuddisasi: "
msgstr "“Is it really true, dear Uttara, that you referred to the offering in this way?” "

msgctxt "dn23:32.11"
msgid "‘imināhaṃ dānena pāyāsiṃ rājaññameva imasmiṃ loke samāgacchiṃ, mā parasmin’”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:32.12"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:32.13"
msgid "“Kissa pana tvaṃ, tāta uttara, dānaṃ datvā evaṃ anuddisasi: "
msgstr "“But why? "

msgctxt "dn23:32.14"
msgid "‘imināhaṃ dānena pāyāsiṃ rājaññameva imasmiṃ loke samāgacchiṃ, mā parasmin’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:32.15"
msgid "Nanu mayaṃ, tāta uttara, puññatthikā dānasseva phalaṃ pāṭikaṅkhino”ti? "
msgstr "Don’t we who seek merit expect some result from the offering?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: pādāpi → pādāsi (mr) 
#. VAR: samphusituṃ → phusituṃ (bj) | chupituṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:32.16"
msgid "“Bhoto kho dāne evarūpaṃ bhojanaṃ dīyati kaṇājakaṃ bilaṅgadutiyaṃ, yaṃ bhavaṃ pādāpi na iccheyya samphusituṃ, kuto bhuñjituṃ, dhorakāni ca vatthāni guḷavālakāni, yāni bhavaṃ pādāpi na iccheyya samphusituṃ, kuto paridahituṃ. "
msgstr "“At your offering such food as rough gruel with pickles was given, which you wouldn’t even want to touch with your foot, much less eat. And also heavy clothes with ball-tails, which you also wouldn’t want to touch with your foot, much less wear. "

msgctxt "dn23:32.17"
msgid "Bhavaṃ kho panamhākaṃ piyo manāpo, kathaṃ mayaṃ manāpaṃ amanāpena saṃyojemā”ti? "
msgstr "Sir, you’re dear and beloved to me. But how can I reconcile one so dear with something so disagreeable?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:32.18"
msgid "“Tena hi tvaṃ, tāta uttara, yādisāhaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjāmi, tādisaṃ bhojanaṃ paṭṭhapehi. "
msgstr "“Well then, dear Uttara, set up an offering with the same kind of food that I eat, "

msgctxt "dn23:32.19"
msgid "Yādisāni cāhaṃ vatthāni paridahāmi, tādisāni ca vatthāni paṭṭhapehī”ti. "
msgstr "and the same kind of clothes that I wear.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:32.20"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho uttaro māṇavo pāyāsissa rājaññassa paṭissutvā yādisaṃ bhojanaṃ pāyāsi rājañño bhuñjati, tādisaṃ bhojanaṃ paṭṭhapesi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Uttara, and did so. "

msgctxt "dn23:32.21"
msgid "Yādisāni ca vatthāni pāyāsi rājañño paridahati, tādisāni ca vatthāni paṭṭhapesi. "
msgstr " "

# NOTE: Cp AN 5.147, AN 9.20
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.356, sc54
#. VAR: acittīkataṃ → apaviddhaṃ (bj) | acittikataṃ (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn23:32.22"
msgid "Atha kho pāyāsi rājañño asakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā asahatthā dānaṃ datvā acittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā apaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajji suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ. "
msgstr "So the chieftain Pāyāsi gave gifts carelessly, thoughtlessly, not with his own hands, giving the dregs. When his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in company with the gods of the Four Great Kings, in an empty palace of acacia. "

msgctxt "dn23:32.23"
msgid "Yo pana tassa dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo. So sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā sahatthā dānaṃ datvā cittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajji devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ. "
msgstr "But the brahmin student Uttara who organized the offering gave gifts carefully, thoughtfully, with his own hands, not giving the dregs. When his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in company with the gods of the Thirty-Three. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn23:32.24"
msgid "6. Pāyāsidevaputta "
msgstr "6. The God Pāyāsi "

# NOTE: Contra MW’s note, divivihara is usually the day’s meditation; siesta is divaseyya
#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs33, pts-vp-pli2.357, sc55
msgctxt "dn23:33.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā gavampati abhikkhaṇaṃ suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ divāvihāraṃ gacchati. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Gavampati would often go to that empty acacia palace for the day’s meditation. "

msgctxt "dn23:33.2"
msgid "Atha kho pāyāsi devaputto yenāyasmā gavampati tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ gavampatiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho pāyāsiṃ devaputtaṃ āyasmā gavampati etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the god Pāyāsi went up to him, bowed, and stood to one side. Gavampati said to him, "

msgctxt "dn23:33.3"
msgid "“kosi tvaṃ, āvuso”ti? "
msgstr "“Who are you, reverend?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:33.4"
msgid "“Ahaṃ, bhante, pāyāsi rājañño”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, I am the chieftain Pāyāsi.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:33.5"
msgid "“Nanu tvaṃ, āvuso, evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahosi: "
msgstr "“Didn’t you have the view that "

msgctxt "dn23:33.6"
msgid "‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’”ti? "
msgstr "there’s no afterlife, no beings are reborn spontaneously, and there’s no fruit or result of good and bad deeds?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:33.7"
msgid "“Saccāhaṃ, bhante, evaṃdiṭṭhiko ahosiṃ: "
msgstr "“It’s true, sir, I did have such a view. "

msgctxt "dn23:33.8"
msgid "‘itipi natthi paro loko, natthi sattā opapātikā, natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:33.9"
msgid "Api cāhaṃ ayyena kumārakassapena etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecito”ti. "
msgstr "But Venerable Kassapa the Prince dissuaded me from that harmful misconception.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:33.10"
msgid "“Yo pana te, āvuso, dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo, so kuhiṃ upapanno”ti? "
msgstr "“But the student named Uttara who organized that offering for you—where has he been reborn?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:33.11"
msgid "“Yo me, bhante, dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo, so sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā sahatthā dānaṃ datvā cittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapanno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyataṃ. "
msgstr "“Sir, Uttara gave gifts carefully, thoughtfully, with his own hands, not giving the dregs. When his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in company with the gods of the Thirty-Three. "

msgctxt "dn23:33.12"
msgid "Ahaṃ pana, bhante, asakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā asahatthā dānaṃ datvā acittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā apaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapanno suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ. "
msgstr "But I gave gifts carelessly, thoughtlessly, not with my own hands, giving the dregs. When my body broke up, after death, I was reborn in company with the gods of the Four Great Kings, in an empty palace of acacia. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn23:33.13"
msgid "Tena hi, bhante gavampati, manussalokaṃ gantvā evamārocehi: "
msgstr "So, sir, when you’ve returned to the human realm, please announce this: "

msgctxt "dn23:33.14"
msgid "‘sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ detha, sahatthā dānaṃ detha, cittīkataṃ dānaṃ detha, anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ detha. "
msgstr "‘Give gifts carefully, thoughtfully, with your own hands, not giving the dregs. "

msgctxt "dn23:33.15"
msgid "Pāyāsi rājañño asakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā asahatthā dānaṃ datvā acittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā apaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapanno suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ. "
msgstr "The chieftain Pāyāsi gave gifts carelessly, thoughtlessly, not with his own hands, giving the dregs. When his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in company with the gods of the Four Great Kings, in an empty palace of acacia. "

msgctxt "dn23:33.16"
msgid "Yo pana tassa dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo, so sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā sahatthā dānaṃ datvā cittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapanno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyatan’”ti. "
msgstr "But the brahmin student Uttara who organized the offering gave gifts carefully, thoughtfully, with his own hands, not giving the dregs. When his body broke up, after death, he was reborn in company with the gods of the Thirty-Three.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs34, pts-vp-pli2.358, sc56
msgctxt "dn23:34.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā gavampati manussalokaṃ āgantvā evamārocesi: "
msgstr "So when Venerable Gavampati returned to the human realm he made that announcement. "

msgctxt "dn23:34.2"
msgid "“sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ detha, sahatthā dānaṃ detha, cittīkataṃ dānaṃ detha, anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ detha. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:34.3"
msgid "Pāyāsi rājañño asakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā asahatthā dānaṃ datvā acittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā apaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā cātumahārājikānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapanno suññaṃ serīsakaṃ vimānaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn23:34.4"
msgid "Yo pana tassa dāne vāvaṭo ahosi uttaro nāma māṇavo, so sakkaccaṃ dānaṃ datvā sahatthā dānaṃ datvā cittīkataṃ dānaṃ datvā anapaviddhaṃ dānaṃ datvā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapanno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ sahabyatan”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn23:34.5"
msgid "Pāyāsisuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "dn23:34.6"
msgid "Mahāvaggo niṭṭhito. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc57
msgctxt "dn23:34.7"
msgid "Mahāpadāna nidānaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn23:34.8"
msgid "nibbānañca sudassanaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn23:34.9"
msgid "Janavasabha govindaṃ, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn23:34.10"
msgid "samayaṃ sakkapañhakaṃ; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "dn23:34.11"
msgid "Mahāsatipaṭṭhānañca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: pāyāsi dasamaṃ bhave → mahāvaggassa saṅgaho (bj, pts1) | mahāvaggoti vuccatīti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn23:34.12"
msgid "pāyāsi dasamaṃ bhave. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endbook">
msgctxt "dn23:34.13"
msgid "Mahāvaggapāḷi niṭṭhitā. "
msgstr ""

